#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:105
msgid "This raises energy prices for everyone"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:107
msgid ""
"\n"
"    On sunny hours the Spanish peninsula often produces more solar than "
"the local grid can absorb. That energy\n"
"    goes unused while other sources (less green, more expensive ones) "
"remain in the mix. Consumers end up paying for flexibility and system\n"
"    constraints twice over. This is measurable, costly, and largely "
"avoidable with better infrastructure\n"
"    and market design.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:115
msgid ""
"\n"
"    <strong>What would help?</strong> Stronger grids, storage (that's "
"batteries!) and price signals that reward\n"
"    using clean power when it is abundant. That reduces waste, eases "
"bills, and puts scarce clean\n"
"    generation to work.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:124
msgid "Put in perspective"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:126
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Today's unused solar total is in the ballpark of the daily "
"electricity of about\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> typical homes, using a reference %(kwh)s "
"kWh per home per day\n"
"    for scale (not a census count — see methodology).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:135
msgid "Methodology"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:137
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Quarter-hourly unused solar (MWh) is derived from Red Eléctrica de "
"España (REE) data, processed in\n"
"    a separate pipeline and stored in this project's database: each row "
"is keyed by date with\n"
"    15-minute buckets of unused energy. Multiple rows for the same day "
"are summed\n"
"    bucket-wise before display.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:145
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The chart aggregates those quarter-hours into 24 hourly bars. Any "
"slots beyond the first 96 are\n"
"    folded into the last hour of the day. Headline day totals and year-"
"to-date figures show the\n"
"    <strong>absolute</strong> net waste (upstream data often stores "
"unused solar as negative MWh).\n"
"    The chart keeps <strong>signed</strong> hourly bars so you can see "
"which hours wasted energy\n"
"    and which did not. “So far this year” sums the absolute daily net "
"from 1 January through the\n"
"    selected date. The average “per hour” line uses that headline day "
"total divided by 24.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:155
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Euro amounts use OMIE peninsula wholesale prices (€/MWh) for each "
"quarter-hour, updated daily\n"
"    from the data pipeline. They are not a bill or settlement, but they "
"show that unused MWh carry\n"
"    real market cost.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:161
msgid "Household analogy"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:163
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The household comparison uses a configurable reference kWh/day figure"
" to give an intuitive\n"
"    scale.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

